  <front>
   <head>EPIGRAM IX. On one who first abused, and then made love to a LADY.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">FOUL — with graceless verse,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The noble — dar'd asperse.</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But when he saw her well bespatter'd,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Her reputation stain'd and tatter'd;</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">He gaz'd and lov'd the hideous elf,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">She look'd so very like himself.</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">True sung the bard well known to fame,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Self-love and social are the same.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
